<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>lay down one’s job • lie down on the job</xh5><p> <i>lay down one’s job</i>—(also: lay down one’s office) resign from a position of power or responsibility: Buddy Darden is just one of the people who was brave enough to <u>lay down his job</u> in Congress.</p><p><i>lie down on the job—</i>be irresponsible or careless in one’s job; fail to work as hard as one should: After a few months ... they get tired of the whole business and <u>lie down on the job</u>.</p> </entry>
